@cowtowncoder You should be able to import the branch from my github repository into an IDE to run the full test. The snippet was just to help for record keeping. 

I'm happy to provide a unit test that aligns with jackson-databind project. The sample I provided was meant to be an easy way to run a full integration test of what was happening rather than be used as a test by Jackson. Note that a dependency on cglib won't work since Spring and Hibernate repackage cglib, but we can mock it.

Would you like me to provide a test for jackson-databind that does not have a dependency?

@cowtowncoder I've sent two PRs

* https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/pull/5356 - This adds the unit tests to 2.x to prevent a regression
* https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/pull/5357 - This merges the previous pull request into 3.x and adds a second commit that fixes it
